title: 110_hr5369
content: In General, Subchapter II of chapter 99 of the Harmonized Tariff Schedule of the United States is amended by inserting new headings for certain products. "New headings for certain products are inserted in Subchapter II of chapter 99 of the Harmonized Tariff Schedule of the United States, including trisubstituted oxazolidinone and naphtho[1,2-." "New headings for certain products are inserted in Subchapter II of chapter 99 of the Harmonized Tariff Schedule of the United States, including benzothiazolium compounds." Benzothiazolium compound (CAS No. 160911-24-0) salt with 4-ethylbenzenesulfonic acid (1:1) provided for in subheading 2934.99.20. Benzoxazolylidene compound with N,N-diethylethanamine (CAS No. 106518-55-2) provided for in subheading 2934.99.20. Copoly[N-(4-sulfamoylphenyl)methacrylamide/methylmethacrylate/acrylonitrile (CAS No. 141634-00-6) (provided for in subheading 9902.01.00). Poly[(ally 2-methyl-2-propenoate)-co-(cyclohexyl 2-hydroxymethyl-2-propenoate)-co-(2-propenoic acid)] (CAS No. 202483-63-4) provided for in subheading 2933.19.90. The curr_chunk is about a chemical compound [(ally 2-methyl-2-propenoate)-co-(2-propenoic acid)] (CAS No. 860399-10-6) provided for in subheading 3208.90.00. The effective date for the amendment applies to articles entered or withdrawn from warehouse for consumption after the 15th day following the enactment of the Act.
